amp of 1776177756294, and the DTLX 5p cron appears to be cut off in the data.\\n\\nLooking at the remaining sessions: the Agent Status cron is running, the Lead direct session has ended, and both the QLHV and DTLX group chats are now done. The stale zombie crons are still lingering, and I'm seeing there are two more cron sessions in the current data that weren't in the baseline. Looking at the session list more carefully, I'm noticing the Lead direct session and DTLX group session both ended and aren't showing up in the current data, while the Agent Status and QLHV group cron are still running. The 14:35 UTC report appears to be sourced from a different cron session than what I was initially tracking, which suggests these are two separate cron instances.\\n\\nComparing the full baseline against what's currently running, I see the same core sessions are still active with no status changes—the QLHV 5p cron, DTLX 5p cron, and Agent Status cron all continue running, and the DTLX group and Lead direct sessions remain in their ended states as expected.\\n\\nThe only thing different this cycle is the `updatedAt` timestamps getting more recent, but that's just normal heartbeat activity. Since there are no actual state transitions, new sessions spawning, or failures occurring, I should stay silent and not send anything.\"\n            },\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Comparing current state (14:42 UTC) against baseline (14:30 UTC):\\n\\n**Baseline:** 3 cron monitors + QLHV group (running) + 2 zombies  \\n**Current:** Same 3 cron monitors + QLHV group (still running) + same zombies — all statuses unchanged\\n\\nThe updatedAt timestamps are advancing normally (14:35→14:39→14:42 for active sessions), but no status transitions, no new sessions, no failures, no blockers.\\n\\n**Silent exit.**\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"ahvholding\",\n          \"model\": \"AHV