hy they're showing similar durations.\n\nLet me recalculate based on the cron schedule: if this cron runs every 5 minutes and the current timestamp is 1776177947, then subtracting 1776177947 - 1776152701 gives about 25246 milliseconds, or roughly 4.2 minutes—meaning this particular run started just a few minutes ago. I'm calculating the elapsed time since each cron job started. The Agent Status cron began at 1776177947 and the current time is 1776177947, so it's just 0 seconds in. The 5p QLHV cron started much earlier at 1776172286 and has been running for about 15 minutes. Let me recalculate the Agent Status cron duration since I have the exact start time now. Converting those milliseconds to minutes gives me roughly 4.2 minutes, so I should verify this calculation with more precision to make sure I'm reporting the duration correctly.\n\nNow I'm going through the other active sessions to get their durations too. The 5p DTLX cron started about 6 hours and 47 minutes ago, and the 5p QLHV cron has been running for around 15 minutes. Everything looks stable across the board, so I should compile this into a status report for the lead.","thinkingSignature":"085eead57fd79a16a232eb67c9912ffe098ffe0e23c09788356fdea02eea01ae"},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the data. Let me compile the status report. Active sessions (excluding this cron):\n- `cron:6f3323ef` (5p DTLX) — running\n- `cron:ed2d0b5d` (5p QLHV) — running\n- `telegram:group:-5163901258` (QLHV group) — running\n\nSending the report to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y5yll5xmxdjc_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 14:45 UTC 14 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• cron:6f3323ef (5p DTLX): running — 5-min progress monitoring (DTLX ecosystem) — ~6h 47m\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (5p QLHV): running — 5-min progress monitoring (QLHV ecosystem) — ~15m\n• telegram:group:-5163901258 (QLHV group): running — QLHV ecosy